# GitHub push target

When the user asks to push, commit-and-push, or sync anything to GitHub:

- Push only to the **izoo2003** repo (`origin` → `https://github.com/izoo2003/Kafi-Sales-Agent.git`).
- Do **not** push to `kafi-group` (`https://github.com/kafi-group/Kafi-Sales-Agent.git`) unless the user explicitly names that org/remote.
- Prefer `git push origin HEAD` (or the current branch’s upstream if it already tracks `origin`).
- If unsure which remote is which, run `git remote -v` and confirm `origin` is `izoo2003` before pushing.
